Chorebus (Chorebus) uliginosus (HALIDAY, 1839)
– 1 f: KU 43. – In Europe widely distributed (
SHENEFELT 1974: 1069
), in Asiatic Russia discovered recently: Irkutsk , Primorski Krai , Sakhalin (
TOBIAS 1998: 377
), reported from Mongolia (
PAPP 2005: 228
). New to the fauna of Korea .
